with ggplot2 we get legends automatically when we use colour or fill option with a variable. There are (at least ) four different ways to remove legends in a plot #rstats
4 ways to remove legends in a plot made with #ggplot2 https://t.co/nTOgzxB5Oc #rstats
third option to remove legend is to use guides with guide_legend() i.e. guides(fill=guide_legend(title=NULL)) #rstats
fourth option to remove legend and my preferred option (if I remember :-)) is to use theme() with     legend.title=element_blank() as arguments. #rstats
second option to remove legend is to use scale_fill_manual(name=NULL) or scale_color_manual(name=NULL) #rstats

One option to remove legend is to use scale_fill_discrete(name=NULL) function when the legend was created with fill argument and scale_color_discrete(name=NULL) when the legend is created with color argument #rstats
